I was drinking. You know
how I get when I drink, sweetheart.

247
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:55,815
- You think it means I don't love you?
- Move.

248
00:12:55,858 --> 00:12:57,400
You can't leave.

249
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,319
I need you.

250
00:13:00,362 --> 00:13:02,781
And you know, I love you.

251
00:13:03,491 --> 00:13:05,825
- Now, look, I made a mistake.
- You don't love me.

252
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:08,203
- Now, baby, come on.
- (CRYING) You don't. You treat me bad,

253
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:09,829
and you beat up on me.

254
00:13:10,372 --> 00:13:12,373
Look, I hit you when you get out of line,

255
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:14,584
and I never just hit you.
I always warn you first,

256
00:13:14,668 --> 00:13:16,461
and then if you don't shape up,
you get whacked.

257
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:18,588
- I'm leaving.
- Now listen, Cecilia,

258
00:13:18,672 --> 00:13:21,341
I don't know who's
filling your head full of these crazy notions,

259
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:22,884
but I've had enough.

260
00:13:24,386 --> 00:13:26,971
I want supper. Get my meatloaf.

261
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:28,389
Uh-uh.

262
00:13:28,432 --> 00:13:31,434
Come on, Cecilia,
you know I can't live without you.

263
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:33,520
I'm like a little kid when it comes to you.

264
00:13:33,562 --> 00:13:35,772
- That's just tough.
- Look, I'm sorry.

265
00:13:35,856 --> 00:13:38,399
I mean, I'm really sorry. Can't I be sorry?

266
00:13:38,442 --> 00:13:39,859
I drink, I get crazy.

267
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:41,402
It's not me. It's the whiskey.

268
00:13:41,445 --> 00:13:43,446
I'm going, Monk, I'm going.

269
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:45,573
Ah, Jesus Christ, I can't reason with you.

270
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:47,909
All right, go ahead.
Let's see how far you get.

271
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:49,744
Go on, go on, you won't last.

272
00:13:49,787 --> 00:13:51,621
You see how it is out in the real world.

273
00:13:51,705 --> 00:13:53,289
Go on, you'll come back.

274
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:56,084
You're just bluff. You're all phony!

275
00:13:56,126 --> 00:13:58,419
You'll be back. It may take a week,

276
00:13:58,504 --> 00:14:01,589
it may take an hour, but you'll be back.

277
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:20,149
(MEN CHATTERING)

278
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:25,113
Oh, jeez, look at all those guys.

279
00:14:26,615 --> 00:14:28,658
Come on, honey, we're gonna make a buck.

280
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:58,563
(MONK SNORING)

281
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:04,068
I ordered bacon and tomato,
you brought me ham and Swiss.

282
00:15:04,653 --> 00:15:06,362
I'll get it right away, ma'am.

283
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:08,239
- Cecilia, I want you to meet somebody.
- Who?

284
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:10,325
Well, remember,
I told you I was going to keep my eyes open

285
00:15:10,367 --> 00:15:11,910
- for eligible men?
- Oh, come on.

286
00:15:11,994 --> 00:15:13,828
- Come on, just keep an open mind.
- Tsk.

287
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:18,291
This is my sister, Cecilia.
This is Mr. Teddy Ashcroft.

288
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:19,834
- How do you do?
- Charmed.

289
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:22,170
Teddy's an exterminator.

290
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:26,341
Right. Merson's Pest Control.
My specialty are mice and silverfish.

291
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:28,760
- I'm pleased to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

292
00:15:28,844 --> 00:15:30,345
CUSTOMER 1: Waitress, please,
my hamburger!

293
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:31,512
- I'm coming.
- CUSTOMER 2: Can we have a check?

294
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:33,556
- I'll be right there. Oh!
- (PLATE BREAKING)

295
00:15:33,641 --> 00:15:36,935
That's it.
That's it, Cecilia, you're fired. Get out!

296
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:39,437
But I'll pay for it. I'll be more careful.

297
00:15:39,521 --> 00:15:42,857
Out. Out.
Take off your apron, go home. You're fired!

298
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:44,484
If she goes, then I go too.

299
00:15:44,526 --> 00:15:45,860
That's fine with me.

300
00:15:45,903 --> 00:15:47,862
She doesn't mean that. No, you've got kids.

301
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:49,030
No, she doesn't mean that.

302
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:51,032
Then tell her to mind her own business.

303
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:52,367
You're fired.

304
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:56,079
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

305
00:16:05,881 --> 00:16:08,925
Ah, back from Egypt.
From the Bedouins to Broadway.

306
00:16:09,009 --> 00:16:11,427
Even though I'm not a religious man,
I hereby vow

307
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:13,346
never to fly over the Atlantic
in bumpy weather,

308
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:16,224
and never to look at another camel.
Drinks anyone?

309
00:16:16,684 --> 00:16:18,351
RITA: Boy, I can't wait
to get out of these clothes

310
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:20,520
and hit some of the night spots.

311
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:22,522
HENRY: Well, children,
let's not waste any time.

312
00:16:22,564 --> 00:16:25,108
The floor show
at the Copacabana starts in 10 minutes,

313
00:16:25,192 --> 00:16:27,402
and we're meeting
the Countess and Larry Wilde.

314
00:16:28,112 --> 00:16:31,197
Well, I am impressed! I really am.

315
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,700
You have yourself quite a place here.

316
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:36,661
You know, I still can't get over the fact
that 24 hours ago,

317
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:38,246
I was in an Egyptian tomb.

318
00:16:38,288 --> 00:16:41,874
I didn't know any of you wonderful people,
and here I am now.

319
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:45,503
I'm on the verge of a
madcap Manhattan weekend.

320
00:16:45,587 --> 00:16:48,589
I hope you like your martinis very dry.

321
00:16:48,632 --> 00:16:49,924
Oh, no, no, thanks.

322
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:52,552
I think I'll wait for
that glass of champagne at the Copacabana.

323
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:02,854
Miss Rita, something on your mind?

324
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:06,232
'Cause you ain't been yourself since you
come back from them pyramids.

325
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:09,110
No, it's nothing. I'll be okay.

326
00:17:09,153 --> 00:17:13,865
I don't suspect it has anything to do
with that explorer fella, Mr. Tom Baxter.

327
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:15,783
Now, why would you say that?

328
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:19,871
The way he speaks, all romantic-like.

329
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:23,499
Yeah. Come on, Delilah, draw my bath.

330
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:25,293
Yes, ma'am.

331
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:29,797
Now, will you be wanting the big bubbles,
or the asses' milk?

332
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:39,098
Boy, I can't wait to get out of these clothes

