00:43:01,996 --> 00:43:03,746
Tell him that you don't love him.

961
00:43:03,831 --> 00:43:04,914
Tell him you can't love him.

962
00:43:04,999 --> 00:43:06,082
He's fictional!

963
00:43:06,166 --> 00:43:08,334
You want to waste your time
with a fictional character?

964
00:43:08,419 --> 00:43:10,670
I mean, you're a sweet girl.
You deserve an actual human.

965
00:43:10,713 --> 00:43:12,422
But Tom's perfect.

966
00:43:12,506 --> 00:43:13,798
Yeah, but he's not real.

967
00:43:13,841 --> 00:43:16,718
What good is perfect if the man's not real?

968
00:43:16,802 --> 00:43:18,428
I can learn to be real.

969
00:43:18,512 --> 00:43:20,305
It's easy. You know, there's nothing to it.

970
00:43:20,347 --> 00:43:22,098
Being real comes very naturally to me.

971
00:43:22,182 --> 00:43:24,434
Can't learn to be real.
It's like learning to be a midget.

972
00:43:24,518 --> 00:43:25,852
It's not a thing you can learn.

973
00:43:25,894 --> 00:43:27,937
Some of us are real, some are not.

974
00:43:28,022 --> 00:43:30,315
I say I can do it.

975
00:43:30,357 --> 00:43:31,941
I'm not going to stay here
and argue with you.

976
00:43:32,026 --> 00:43:33,192
I'm gonna go back to town.

977
00:43:33,277 --> 00:43:36,362
I'm going to call my attorney,
the Actors' Union.

978
00:43:36,864 --> 00:43:38,615
I won't take this lying down.

979
00:43:38,699 --> 00:43:42,577
Nor will Raoul Hirsch, nor the police,

980
00:43:42,661 --> 00:43:44,662
nor the FBI.

981
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:48,166
Yes, yes, we found him.

982
00:43:48,834 --> 00:43:50,209
Gil Shepherd found him,

983
00:43:50,294 --> 00:43:52,587
but he refuses to get back on the screen.

984
00:43:52,671 --> 00:43:54,672
R.H. is very upset.

985
00:43:54,715 --> 00:43:58,176
No, no, we can't force him. It's not a crime.

986
00:43:58,218 --> 00:44:00,053
We need a plan.

987
00:44:00,095 --> 00:44:01,888
Yeah, the press is on our side.

988
00:44:01,972 --> 00:44:04,599
It took a few bucks,
but they're going to keep it quiet for now.

989
00:44:04,683 --> 00:44:07,352
Uh, what? Really?

990
00:44:09,104 --> 00:44:11,773
The Tom Baxter character
in a movie house in Chicago

991
00:44:11,857 --> 00:44:13,900
has been forgetting his lines.

992
00:44:13,942 --> 00:44:16,361
I just got a call from the manager.

993
00:44:16,403 --> 00:44:18,946
If anybody wants me,
I'll be in the bathroom.

994
00:44:19,031 --> 00:44:20,907
On the floor, weeping.

995
00:44:23,911 --> 00:44:26,663
I mean, you do...
Aren't you at all even worried?

996
00:44:26,747 --> 00:44:29,248
Well, what about
Raoul Hirsch and what, the FBI?

997
00:44:29,333 --> 00:44:31,417
No, Cecilia,
if I can be with you, I'm never going back.

998
00:44:31,502 --> 00:44:33,002
- But I, you know...
- No more buts.

999
00:44:33,087 --> 00:44:35,213
I said I was going
to learn about the real world with you.

1000
00:44:35,255 --> 00:44:36,506
Show me.

1001
00:44:40,594 --> 00:44:42,887
(INAUDIBLE)

1002
00:45:19,842 --> 00:45:23,720
TOM: It's beautiful.
But I'm not sure exactly what it is.

1003
00:45:23,804 --> 00:45:28,099
Oh, this is a church.
You do believe in God, don't you?

1004
00:45:28,142 --> 00:45:29,976
Meaning?

1005
00:45:30,060 --> 00:45:35,732
Mmm, the reason for everything,
the, the world, the universe...

1006
00:45:35,816 --> 00:45:36,816
Oh, I think I know what you mean.

1007
00:45:36,900 --> 00:45:39,152
The two men who wrote, uh,
The Purple Rose of Cairo.

1008
00:45:39,236 --> 00:45:42,155
Irving Sachs and R.H. Levine,
the writers who collaborate on films.

1009
00:45:42,239 --> 00:45:45,491
No, no, I'm talking
about something much bigger than that.

1010
00:45:45,534 --> 00:45:49,203
No, think for a minute.
A reason for everything.

1011
00:45:49,288 --> 00:45:52,498
Otherwise, it'd be
like a movie with no point,

1012
00:45:52,583 --> 00:45:53,833
and no happy ending.

1013
00:45:53,876 --> 00:45:55,501
So there you are!

1014
00:45:56,128 --> 00:45:57,628
I'm looking for you.

1015
00:45:57,671 --> 00:45:59,714
Monk, I, um...

1016
00:46:01,091 --> 00:46:04,761
This is my husband. This is Tom Baxter.

1017
00:46:04,845 --> 00:46:07,972
Adventurer, explorer, the Chicago Baxters.
I'm charmed to meet you.

1018
00:46:08,015 --> 00:46:10,141
So you wear the britches.

1019
00:46:10,184 --> 00:46:11,768
CECILIA: What did you want
to talk to me about?

1020
00:46:11,852 --> 00:46:14,604
I heard you were out on the town last night.

1021
00:46:14,688 --> 00:46:18,024
Yeah, I'm sorry.
I admit I didn't tell the truth about that,

1022
00:46:18,066 --> 00:46:21,027
but things have
been so strange the last 24 hours...

1023
00:46:21,069 --> 00:46:22,403
You know what I told you I'd do to you

1024
00:46:22,488 --> 00:46:23,780
- if you ever lied to me?
- Monk, don't hit me.

1025
00:46:23,864 --> 00:46:25,948
Obviously, your marriage
has come to an impasse, sir.

1026
00:46:26,033 --> 00:46:27,533
And you keep out of this.

1027
00:46:27,618 --> 00:46:29,827
- Monk, let's just talk.
- No, you're coming home with me!

1028
00:46:29,870 --> 00:46:31,412
- Can't we talk?
- Perhaps you don't understand, sir,

1029
00:46:31,497 --> 00:46:32,538
but I'm in love with your wife.

1030
00:46:32,623 --> 00:46:34,123
Close your yap, jackass.

1031
00:46:34,208 --> 00:46:35,208
Now let's go. You're in for a lesson...

1032
00:46:35,292 --> 00:46:37,210
You're failing to understand, sir.

1033
00:46:37,294 --> 00:46:38,377
She's not coming with you.

1034
00:46:38,420 --> 00:46:40,630
- Oh, she's not, huh?
- No, you take your hands off.

1035
00:46:40,714 --> 00:46:42,715
No man will hit the woman I love,
nor any woman.

1036
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:46,219
- Beat it! Beat it. I'm gonna take you apart!
- Stop it!

1037
00:46:46,261 --> 00:46:48,012
- He's got a terrible temper.
- And you, go home.

1038
00:46:48,055 --> 00:46:51,307
Sorry, it's written into my character.
Courage.

1039
00:46:51,391 --> 00:46:52,600
Stop it!

1040
00:47:00,692 --> 00:47:03,194
- Come on.
- Stop it! What are you doing?

1041
00:47:15,082 --> 00:47:16,415
Time for the old one-two.

1042
00:47:16,458 --> 00:47:18,000
(GRUNTING)

1043
00:47:19,795 --> 00:47:21,587
Hope he's had enough.

1044
00:47:22,005 --> 00:47:24,298
Sorry, pal. Sorry about the rough stuff.

1045
00:47:24,383 --> 00:47:25,508
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1046
00:47:25,592 --> 00:47:26,926
Let me give you a hand. There's a...

1047
00:47:26,969 --> 00:47:30,429
(GRUNTING) God, it's not fair. Oh!

1048
00:47:34,476 --> 00:47:36,853
Tom! What are you doing?

1049
00:47:37,396 --> 00:47:39,564
- You're coming home with me now.
- No, I'm not!

1050
00:47:39,606 --> 00:47:40,606
What'd you say?

1051
00:47:40,691 --> 00:47:42,650
No, I'm going to stay
and see that Tom's okay.

1052
00:47:42,734 --> 00:47:43,943
- I...
- You're a bully, Monk.

1053
00:47:43,986 --> 00:47:44,986
I gave you an order.

1054
00:47:45,070 --> 00:47:46,863
I don't care. I'm tired of taking your orders.

1055
00:47:46,947 --> 00:47:48,072
You could've killed him.

1056
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:50,658
All right. I'm sorry. I didn't mean it.

1057
00:47:50,742 --> 00:47:51,742
- I hit hard.
- You can't just...

1058
00:47:51,785 --> 00:47:53,995
You can't just
go through life beating people up.

1059
00:47:54,079 --> 00:47:56,080
Look, I'm telling you one more time.
Are you coming with me?

1060
00:47:56,123 --> 00:47:57,540
No, I'm not.

1061
00:47:58,500 --> 00:48:00,376
I'm telling you one more time. You coming?

1062
00:48:00,460 --> 00:48:02,795
- No! No, I'm not!
- Come on!

1063
00:48:04,798 --> 00:48:07,633
The hell with it. I need a beer anyway.

1064
00:48:07,718 --> 00:48:09,468
I'll see you later.

1065
00:48:12,139 --> 00:48:14,056
Oh, are you okay?

1066
00:48:14,141 --> 00:48:16,475
Oh, oh, yeah. I'm fine.

1067
00:48:16,560 --> 00:48:17,727
You're not even marked.

1068
00:48:17,811 --> 00:48:19,645
Your hair is in place.

1069
00:48:19,730 --> 00:48:21,480
No, no. I don't get hurt or bleed.

1070
00:48:21,523 --> 00:48:22,607
Hair doesn't muss.

1071
00:48:22,649 --> 00:48:24,817
It's one of the advantages
of being imaginary.

1072
00:48:24,860 --> 00:48:26,569
- (CHUCKLES)
- You were very brave.

1073
00:48:26,653 --> 00:48:30,406
Yeah, well, I had him, too,
till he started fighting dirty.

1074
00:48:30,490 --> 00:48:33,534
That's why you'll never
survive off the screen.

1075
00:48:33,619 --> 00:48:36,996
You were pretty brave, too.
You stood right up to him.

1076
00:48:37,039 --> 00:48:38,664
You inspired me.

1077
00:48:51,845 --> 00:48:53,596
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1078
00:48:54,806 --> 00:48:56,015
CECILIA: Mr. Shepherd.

1079
00:48:56,099 --> 00:48:59,185
Oh, Cecilia, look, I got to speak to you.

1080
00:48:59,227 --> 00:49:01,979
Oh, listen, I've had a crazy morning.

1081
00:49:02,022 --> 00:49:04,273
- I'm still shaking.
- Look, I don't know what to do, all right?

1082
00:49:04,358 --> 00:49:05,775
I've struggled my whole life.

1083
00:49:05,859 --> 00:49:08,069
And now I'm
finally beginning to break through

1084
00:49:08,153 --> 00:49:09,946
and my whole career's
going right down the drain.

1085
00:49:10,030 --> 00:49:12,490
You don't have to worry about that.

1086
00:49:12,532 --> 00:49:15,368
You'll always be a great movie star.

1087
00:49:15,452 --> 00:49:20,122
Oh, well, that's very nice of you to say,
but technically, I'm not really a star yet.

1088
00:49:20,207 --> 00:49:24,251
(CHUCKLING) Cecilia, you know, I mean,
I try to carry myself like one.

1089
00:49:24,336 --> 00:49:27,338
You know, I do the best I can
as far as that, but star?

1090
00:49:27,381 --> 00:49:30,091
Phew! That's a big word, isn't it? Star?

1091
00:49:30,717 --> 00:49:32,969
Yeah, uh, no, no.

1092
00:49:33,053 --> 00:49:34,428
No, star, no, no.

1093
00:49:34,513 --> 00:49:39,100
And you're not just a pretty face,
you're also a peach of an actor.

1094
00:49:39,184 --> 00:49:41,686
Really, I've seen you. I've seen you a lot.

1095
00:49:41,728 --> 00:49:43,562
You've got something.

1096
00:49:44,398 --> 00:49:45,564
- Is that your opinion?
- Sure.

1097
00:49:45,649 --> 00:49:47,400
And I see all the movies.

1098
00:49:47,484 --> 00:49:51,153
You've got, oh, how can I describe it?

1099
00:49:53,073 --> 00:49:55,241
You've got a magical glow.

1100
00:49:55,325 --> 00:49:57,743
(CHUCKLING) Oh, boy. Oh, oh.

1101
00:49:57,828 --> 00:50:01,414
To hear that from a real person,
that is just...

1102
00:50:01,456 --> 00:50:03,165
(EXHALING) It's not
one of those movie colony bimbos,

1103
00:50:03,250 --> 00:50:06,711
you know, with the fancy dresses,
filling you full of hot air.

1104
00:50:06,753 --> 00:50:08,629
Would you get over here
and sit down, please?

1105
00:50:08,714 --> 00:50:10,881
Oh, you know, you can take it from me.

1106
00:50:10,924 --> 00:50:12,425
You're not just a flash in the pan.

1107
00:50:12,509 --> 00:50:15,928
No, you know, it'd be very easy
for me to trade on my looks.

1108
00:50:16,013 --> 00:50:17,054
- Just, like that.
- Oh, sure.

1109
00:50:17,097 --> 00:50:18,764
But I have some serious acting ambitions.

1110
00:50:18,849 --> 00:50:20,933
You should. You should.

1111
00:50:21,018 --> 00:50:24,270
You, you know...
I think you're great in all the funny movies.

1112
00:50:24,354 --> 00:50:25,604
Thank you.

1113
00:50:25,689 --> 00:50:26,814
Really, I was thinking you should,

1114
00:50:26,898 --> 00:50:29,316
you should
play some of the more heroic parts.

1115
00:50:29,401 --> 00:50:30,401
I want...

1116
00:50:30,444 --> 00:50:32,153
- I tell my agent that a hundred times!
- Yeah?

1117
00:50:32,237 --> 00:50:35,114
Well, you know, well, you could play...

1118
00:50:35,157 --> 00:50:37,783
You could play,
like, Daniel Boone, or someone...

1119
00:50:37,868 --> 00:50:39,535
- Lindbergh! Oh...
- Oh!

1120
00:50:39,619 --> 00:50:41,412
- You'd be wonderful as Lindbergh.
- My God!

1121
00:50:41,455 --> 00:50:43,456
- You are a mind reader.
- We had the same thought?

1122
00:50:43,498 --> 00:50:46,208
- Really?
- I am on the verge of signing for that part.

1123
00:50:46,293 --> 00:50:48,627
- No! Really?
- I'm, I am! I can taste it.

1124
00:50:48,670 --> 00:50:50,504
Oh, you'll be wonderful.

1125
00:50:50,589 --> 00:50:53,132
- Well, thank you.
- Oh, there's something inside you that...

1126
00:50:53,175 --> 00:50:56,510
You have that
same kind of lone heroic quality.

1127
00:50:56,595 --> 00:50:59,138
You're exactly right.
Everyone has been telling me not to...

1128
00:50:59,222 --> 00:51:00,598
- You are right.
- Don't you listen.

1129
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:02,975
Basically, I have been a loner my entire life.

1130
00:51:03,060 --> 00:51:04,643
Well, sure, anyone can see that.

1131
00:51:04,686 --> 00:51:07,772
You know, you're deep
and probably complicated.

1132
00:51:08,690 --> 00:51:10,149
Can I buy you lunch?

1133
00:51:10,233 --> 00:51:11,609
- Me?
- Please. Can I?

1134
00:51:11,651 --> 00:51:12,818
Please. Look, I love... I love talking to you.

1135
00:51:12,861 --> 00:51:13,986
Oh, uh, I was just going to go upstairs...

1136
00:51:14,071 --> 00:51:15,821
- Don't, no, really, come on...
- Really?

1137
00:51:15,864 --> 00:51:18,324
- I open myself up around you...
- Oh...

1138
00:51:18,366 --> 00:51:19,825
Have you ever been to Hollywood?

1139
00:51:19,868 --> 00:51:21,243
Uh, come on, no, of course not.

1140
00:51:21,328 --> 00:51:23,871
You, well, I would
love to just take you around Hollywood.

1141
00:51:23,955 --> 00:51:25,331
- I would real...
- Oh.

1142
00:51:25,415 --> 00:51:26,999
- Could I make a confession?
- Sure.

1143
00:51:27,042 --> 00:51:29,210
Look, my real name, it's not Gil Shepherd.

1144
00:51:29,294 --> 00:51:31,629
- It's Herman Bardebedian.
- Really?

1145
00:51:31,671 --> 00:51:35,132
I've, yeah, I've been a cab driver for about...

1146
00:51:35,175 --> 00:51:37,968
- Boy, do you have a pretty face.
- Come on.

1147
00:51:38,011 --> 00:51:39,678
- You do!
- Oh.

1148
00:51:54,861 --> 00:51:56,529
EMMA: Hi, big boy.

1149
00:51:58,573 --> 00:52:00,324
You alone?

1150
00:52:00,367 --> 00:52:01,700
Oh, hello.

1151
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:06,664
Uh, well, I'm alone for now,
but later I have an appointment,

1152
00:52:06,706 --> 00:52:08,833
or should I say rendezvous?

1153
00:52:09,543 --> 00:52:11,001
Good for you.

1154
00:52:11,711 --> 00:52:14,046
Where did you get the funny suit?

1155
00:52:14,714 --> 00:52:16,882
- What, this?
- Yeah.

1156
00:52:17,717 --> 00:52:19,718
You coming from a costume party?

1157
00:52:19,803 --> 00:52:21,137
(LAUGHING)

1158
00:52:21,805 --> 00:52:25,141
No, no, I'm Tom Baxter
of the Chicago Baxters.

1159
00:52:25,225 --> 00:52:27,935
Explorer, poet, adventurer.
Just back from Cairo

1160
00:52:28,019 --> 00:52:31,438
where I searched
in vain for the legendary purple rose.

1161
00:52:32,232 --> 00:52:33,774
How about that?

1162
00:52:34,192 --> 00:52:35,693
Well, uh, who are you?

1163
00:52:35,735 --> 00:52:38,237
- My name's Emma.
- Oh, that's lovely.

1164
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:39,822
What do you do, Emma?

1165
00:52:39,906 --> 00:52:41,574
I'm a working girl.

1166
00:52:41,658 --> 00:52:43,993
And what do you do, you delicate creature?

1167
00:52:44,077 --> 00:52:46,787
(CHUCKLING) Anything that'll make a buck.

1168
00:52:47,706 --> 00:52:51,083
Well, we Baxters
never really had to worry about money.

1169
00:52:51,168 --> 00:52:54,128
I'll bet. You want to come along with me?

1170
00:52:54,796 --> 00:52:56,422
Where to, Emma?

1171
00:52:56,506 --> 00:52:59,675
Where I work.
I think you might have a good time.

1172
00:53:00,677 --> 00:53:03,846
Sounds enchanting.
I'm up for new experiences.

1173
00:53:03,930 --> 00:53:05,431
I may be able to help.

1174
00:53:08,226 --> 00:53:09,935
EMMA: Hi, girls. This is Tom.

1175
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:11,187
Hi there, ladies.

1176
00:53:11,271 --> 00:53:12,771
Don't you all look enticing?

1177
00:53:12,856 --> 00:53:14,523
I know what you want.

1178
00:53:14,608 --> 00:53:17,776
You want to be the great white hunter
and you want me to be the tiger.

1179
00:53:17,861 --> 00:53:21,071
(CHUCKLING) Uh, I don't get it.

1180
00:53:21,114 --> 00:53:22,740
You will if you can afford it.

1181
00:53:22,782 --> 00:53:24,617
I met Tom out at the amusement park.

1182
00:53:24,659 --> 00:53:26,702
Oh, no, that's, uh, my hat.

1183
00:53:27,787 --> 00:53:30,497
Uh, yes, I was, uh...
I was thinking about something.

1184
00:53:30,582 --> 00:53:33,459
- I can imagine.
- Two of us at the same time?

1185
00:53:33,543 --> 00:53:35,461
You know, I was
thinking about some very deep things.

1186
00:53:35,545 --> 00:53:39,298
About God and his relation
with Irving Sachs and R.H. Levine.

1187
00:53:39,341 --> 00:53:41,967
And, I was thinking about life in general.

1188
00:53:42,052 --> 00:53:44,303
The... The origin
of everything we see about us.

1189
00:53:44,387 --> 00:53:47,973
The, uh... The finality
of death and how almost magical

1190
00:53:48,058 --> 00:53:51,518
it seems in the... In the real world as, uh...
As opposed to the world of

1191
00:53:51,603 --> 00:53:53,479
celluloid and flickering shadows.

1192
00:53:53,563 --> 00:53:55,272
Where did you find this clown?

1193
00:53:55,315 --> 00:53:57,483
For example, the miracle of birth.

1194
00:53:57,525 --> 00:53:59,777
Now. I suppose
some of you lovely ladies are married.

1195
00:53:59,819 --> 00:54:01,570
- Not anymore.
